TY  - JOUR
AU  - Cochrane, John H.
AU  - Longstaff, Francis A.
AU  - Santa-Clara, Pedro
T1  - Two Trees
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhm059
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 21
IS  - 1
SP  - 347
EP  - 385
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We solve a model with two i.i.d. Lucas trees. Although the corresponding one-tree model produces a constant price-dividend ratio and i.i.d. returns, the two-tree model produces interesting asset-pricing dynamics. Investors want to rebalance their portfolios after any change in value. Because the size of the trees is fixed, prices must adjust to offset this desire. As a result, expected returns, excess returns, and return volatility all vary through time. Returns display serial correlation and are predictable from price-dividend ratios. Return volatility differs from cash-flow volatility, and return shocks can occur without news about cash flows.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhm059
ER  - 



